                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.796/393a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-09T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 9, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>175. Clayton requests following be communicated to Morgan:</p>
                <p>“The telegram from you sent on the 5th of August was received on the 8th.<note
                        n="61" xml:id="d226fn61">No. 212, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> It is
                    believed that every endeavor should be made by you to have the purchase of
                    assets and equipment of Sedta brought about at a price which will be as low as
                    possible. Such price should not be more than $150,000 and should be on terms
                    mentioned in discussion with you before you left. Please let us know if this is
                    not possible. With reference to the telegram dated August 6,<note n="62"
                        xml:id="d226fn62">Not printed.</note> please report the extent of free
                    transportation which Panagra provided as well as what further amount of such
                    transportation would be desired.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
